{@--2@} To make;  
{#gaRikAmavaroDamakarot#} Dk; {#nfpeRa cakre#} 
{#yuvarAjaSabdaBAk#} <ls>R. 3. 35</ls>; {#yuvarAjaH kftaH#} &c.

{@--5@} To produce, cause,
engender; {#ratimuBayaprArTanA kurute#}  
<ls>Ś. 2. 1.</ls>

{@--10@} To carry
out, execute, obey; {#evaM kriyate#} 
{#yuzmadAdeSaH#} <ls>Māl. 1</ls>; or {#karizyAmi vacastava#}
or {#SAsanaM me kuruzva#} &c.

{@--11@} To bring
about, accomplish, effect; {#satsaMgatiH#}
{#kaTaya kiM na karoti pusAM#} <ls>Bh. 2. 23.</ls>

{@--15@} To
place or put on (with <ab>loc.</ab>); {#kaMWe#} 
{#hAramakaret#} <ls>K. 212</ls>; {#pARimurasi kftvA#} &c.

{@--16@} To entrust (with some duty),
appoint; {#aDyakzAn viviDAnkuryAttatra#}
{#tatra vipaScitaH#} <ls>Ms. 7. 81.</ls>

{@--18@} To think,
regard, consider;  
{#dfzwistfRIkftajagattrayasattvasArA#} <ls>U. 6. 19.</ls>

{@--19@} To take (as
in the hand); {#kuru kare#} 
{#gurumekamayoGanaM#} <ls>N. 4. 59.</ls>

{@--20@} To make a
sound, as in {#KAtkftya, PUtkftya#}
{#BuMkte#}; so {#vazawakf, svAhAkf#} &c.

{@--21@} To
pass, spend (time); {#varzARi daSa cakruH#}
spent; {#kzaRaM kuru#} wait a moment.

{@--22@}
To direct towards, turn the 
attention to, resolve on; (with <ab>loc.</ab> or
<ab>dat.</ab>); {#nADarme kurute manaH#} <ls>Ms. 12. 118</ls>;
{#nagaragamanAya matiM na karoti#} <ls>Ś. 2.</ls>

{@--23@}
To do a thing for another, either
for his advantage or injury;  
{#prAptAgninirvApaRagarvamaMbu ratnAMkurajyotizi kiM#}
{#karoti#} <ls>Vikr. 1. 18</ls>; {#yadanena kftaM mayi#},
{#asO kiM me karizyati#} &c.

{@--24@} To use,
employ, make use of; {#kiM tayA kriyate#}
{#DenvA#} <ls>Pt. 1.</ls>

{@--36@} To make like,
consider equal to, <ab>cf.</ab> {#tfRIkf#} (said
to be <ab>Atm.</ab> only in the last 10
senses). This root is often used
with nouns, adjectives, and 
indeclinables to form verbs from them, 
somewhat like the English affixes ‘en’
or ‘(i) fy’, in the sense of ‘making
a person or thing to be what it
previously is not’; {%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#kfzRIkf#} to
make that which is not already
black, black, {%<ab>i. e.</ab>%} blacken; so  
{#SvetIkf#} to whiten; {#GanIkf#} to solidify;
{#viralIkf#} to rarefy &c. &c. 
Sometimes these formations take place
in other senses also; {%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#kroqIkf#}
‘to clasp to the bosom’, embrace
{#BasmIkf#} to reduce to ashes; {#pravaRIkf#}
to incline, bend; {#tfRIkf#} to value as
little as straw; {#maMdIkf#} to slacken,
make slow; so {#SUlAkf#} to roast on
the end of pointed lances; {#suKAkf#}
to please; {#samayAkf#} to spend time &c.
{%<ab>N. B.</ab>%} This root by itself admits of
either Pada; but it is <ab>Atm.</ab> 
generally with prepositions in the following
senses:--(1) doing injury to; (2)
censure, blame; (3) serving; (4)
outraging, acting violently or rashly;
(5) preparing, changing the 
condition of, turning into; (6) reciting.
(7) employing, using; see  
<ls>P. I. 3. 32</ls> and “Student's Guide to Sanskrit
Composition” § 338. {%Note%}. The root
{#kf#} is of the most frequent application
in Sanskrit literature, and its senses
are variously modified, or almost 
infinitely extended, according to the
noun with which the root is 
connected; {%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#padaM kf#} to set foot (<ab>fig.</ab> also);
{#ASrame padaM karizyasi#} <ls>Ś. 4. 19</ls>; {#krameRa#}
{#kftaM mama vapuzi navayOvanena padaM#} <ls>K. 141</ls>;  
{#manasA kf#} to think of, meditate; {#manasi kf#}
to think; {#dfzwvA manasyevamakarot#} <ls>K. 136</ls>;
or to resolve or determine; {#saKyaM, mEtrIM#}
{#kf#} to form friendship with; {#astrARi#}
{#kf#} to practise the use of weapons;
{#daMqaM kf#} to inflict punishment; {#hfdaye kf#} 

to pay heed to; {#kAlaM kf#} to die; {#matiM#}
{#dudDiM-kf#} to think of, intend, mean;
{#udakaM kf#} to offer libations of water to
the Manes; {#ciraM kf#} to delay; {#darduraM kf#}
to play on the lute; {#naKAni kf#} to
clean the nails; {#kanyAM kf#} to 
outrage or violate a maiden; {#vinA kf#}
to separate from, to be abandoned
by, as in {#madanena vinAkftA ratiH#}  
<ls>Ku. 4. 21</ls>; {#maDye kf#} to place in the middle,
to have reference to; {#maDyekftya sTitaM#}
{#kraTakESikAn#} <ls>M. 5. 2</ls>; {#vaSe kf#} to win
over, place in subjection, subdue;
{#camatkf#} to cause surprise; make an
exhibition or a show; {#satkf#} to honour,
treat with respect; {#tiryakkf#} to place
aside.

To cause
to do, perform, make, execute &c.;
{#AjYAM kAraya rakzeBiH#} <ls>Bk. 8. 84</ls>; {#BftyaM#} 
{#Bftyena vA kawaM kArayati#} <ls>Sk.</ls>
